quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  11,61,"And to Thamood their brother Salih; he said, 'O my people, serve God! You have no god other than He. It is He who produced you from the earth and has given you to live therein; so ask forgiveness of Him, then repent to Him; surely my Lord is nigh, and answers prayer"
  11,62,"They said, 'Salih, thou hast hitherto been a source of hope among us. What, dost thou forbid us to serve that our fathers served? Truly we are in doubt, concerning what thou callest us to, disquieting"
  11,63,"He said, 'O my people, what think you? If I stand upon a clear sign from my Lord, and He has given me mercy from Him, who shall help me against God if I rebel against Him? You would do nothing for me, except increase my loss"
  11,64,"O my people, this is the She-camel of God, to be a sign for you. Leave her that she may eat in God's earth, and touch her not with evil, lest you' be seized by a nigh chastisement"
  11,65,"But they hamstrung her; and he said, 'Take your joy in your habitation three days -- that is a promise not to be belied"
  11,66,"And when Our command came, We delivered Salih and those who believed with him by a mercy from Us, and from the degradation of that day; thy Lord is the All-strong, the All-mighty"
  11,67,"And the evildoers were seized by the Cry, and morning found them in their habitations fallen prostrate"
  11,68,"as if they never dwelt there: 'Surely Thamood disbelieved in their Lord, so away with Thamood"